      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments conducted with bovine blood at 37°C, hematocrit 33±2%, and documented flow rates measured with calibrated Coriolis flow meters (±0.5% accuracy). All boundary conditions in CFD model set to match experimental values. Temperature variation within ±0.5°C across test runs; viscosity variation accounted for in sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (mean relative error, RH index) computed and documented for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH values computed from CFD shear stress fields using the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model. Comparison against experimental NIH measurements yields mean relative error of 8.3% and maximum of 14.1%, both within the 15% acceptance threshold. RH index computed relative to predicate device baseline; all five conditions satisfy RH < 1.0."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, RH index, pressure head) directly map to the regulatory decision criterion and clinical hemolysis risk.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are the FDA-recognized metrics for blood pump hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. Pressure head validates hydraulic performance relevant to CPB clinical efficacy. Both QoIs are directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinical risk of hemolysis-induced complications."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating range as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry — identical to the device geometry used in the COU. Operating conditions span the full clinical CPB range (2.5–6.0 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). Bovine blood used as the test fluid, consistent with FDA-accepted hemolysis testing protocols. Geometry fidelity confirmed by coordinate measurement machine inspection of test article."
    },
